<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910213-0089</DOCNO><DOCID>910213-0089.</DOCID><HL>   REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:   To Err Is Human</HL><DATE>02/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12</SO><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><LP>   Federal appeals court Judge Harvie Wilkinson III reversedthe harsh 45-year jail term given to Jim Bakker, the formertelevision evangelist, because the trial judge said duringsentencing that Rev. Bakker &quot;had no thought whatever abouthis victims and those of us who do have a religion areridiculed as being saps.&quot; The ruling orders that Mr. Bakkerbe resentenced. Judge Wilkinson said, &quot;The imposition of alengthy prison term here may have reflected the fact that thecourt's own sense of religious propriety had somehow beenbetrayed.&quot; Hmmm. We seem to recall that in sentencing MichaelMilken, Judge Kimba Wood went on at some length about &quot;adecade of greed&quot; and other nonlegal concepts.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>